title: New Hampshire Election Results
title_page: New Hampshire Election Results - The New York Times
maintext:
Joseph R. Biden Jr. won New Hampshire's four electoral votes despite President Trump’s push to take back the state after losing it to Hillary Clinton by only 2,736 votes in 2016. Read more
New Hampshire’s reputation as a battleground state was solidified this year in the primaries, when voters put two popular incumbents — a Republican governor and a Democratic senator — back on the ballot.
Both the governor, Chris Sununu, and the senator, Jeanne Shaheen, won re-election. Mr. Sununu was being challenged by Dan Feltes, the majority leader of the State Senate, who defeated a Bernie Sanders-backed opponent in the Democratic primary. Ms. Shaheen, a former governor and two-term senator, squared off against Corky Messner, a lawyer who has been endorsed by Mr. Trump, but has been attacked by critics who say he has few ties to New Hampshire.
— NICHOLAS BOGEL-BURROUGHS Read less
